  "instructions": [
    "1. Preheat grill to medium-high heat.",
    "2. In a large bowl, whisk together peanut sauce, soy sauce, brown sugar, fish sauce, and garlic powder.",
    "3. Add chicken to the bowl and toss to coat with the sauce.",
    "4. Thread chicken onto skewers, leaving a small space between each piece.",
    "5. Brush grill with oil to prevent sticking.",
    "6. Grill chicken for 8-10 minutes, turning frequently, until cooked through.",
    "7. Meanwhile, grill red bell peppers for 5-7 minutes, until slightly charred.",
    "8. Serve chicken skewers with roasted red peppers, cucumber, and carrot sticks.",
    "9. Garnish with fresh cilantro, if desired.",
    "10. Serve immediately and enjoy!"
